sec.p:
Information from the Hajj 2009 showing low rates of pH1N1 suggests that:



Older pilgrims had some cross-immunity to pH1N1 from previous H1N1 influenza A infection;


Many with known risk factors, including pregnant women, heeded the official advice from the Ministry of Hajj to avoid Hajj 2009;


Control measures worked;


Targeted information and advice achieved voluntary limitation of exposure in those at particular risk of influenza.
